The following example should not show errors, even if you have no master.

SQL:

CHANGE MASTER TO 
MASTER_HOST = '162.100.100.100', 
MASTER_USER = 'slave01', 
MASTER_PASSWORD='somepwd', 
MASTER_PORT = 5000, 
MASTER_LOG_FILE = 'binlog.000031', 
MASTER_LOG_POS = 3234; 
START SLAVE;
STOP SLAVE;
CHANGE MASTER TO MASTER_PASSWORD = 'my_new_pwd';
START SLAVE;
SHOW SLAVE STATUS \G
STOP SLAVE;
RESET SLAVE;
START SLAVE;
